    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared components are the single source of truth. CalendarSidePane MUST consume `@spaarke/events-components` — no local divergent copies allowed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 only — no hex, no rgba, no v8. Verify the shared `CalendarSection` already complies. Dark-mode parity test REQUIRED.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 (CalendarSidePane is in `src/solutions/*` which is React 19 per ADR-022 Code Pages). No React 18-only fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ZERO behavioral OR visual regression on CalendarSidePane record-form rendering. If divergence between local and shared `CalendarSection` exists (different props/defaults), the unification MUST resolve it via the shared lib's canonical form OR be documented and operator-approved.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If the shared lib's `CalendarSection` has a different prop signature than the local copy, the CalendarSidePane App MUST adapt to the shared signature (not the other way — the shared lib is canonical).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Verify export: `@spaarke/events-components` must already export `CalendarSection` from its public `index.ts`. If it doesn't, add the export — but verify this doesn't introduce a circular dep.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Bundle-size impact (NFR-08): CalendarSidePane bundle size MAY change (the shared lib import path might bring in additional shared utilities). Measure before/after; if delta &gt; +50 KB, justify in notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

