  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor declaration">Output rigor declaration: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — frontend + refactoring + fluent-ui tags, visual parity required, ADR-021 dark-mode check. Step 9.5 quality gates MANDATORY.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Diff the two CalendarSection files">Read both `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/src/components/CalendarSection.tsx` and `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/components/CalendarSection/CalendarSection.tsx`. Diff prop signatures, default values, className strategy, event handling, theming. Document divergence in `notes/b6-pre-change-diff.md`.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Pre-change visual snapshot">Open CalendarSidePane on a record form (Matter/Project/Contract) in both light and dark mode. Capture screenshots OR detailed written description. Stash in `notes/b6-pre-change-snapshot.md`.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify export">Read `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/index.ts` — confirm `CalendarSection` is exported. If not, add the export. Check for circular deps.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update App.tsx import">Edit `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/src/App.tsx`: replace local import (`from './components/CalendarSection'`) with shared lib import (`from '@spaarke/events-components'`). Verify the imported component accepts the props CalendarSidePane currently passes; adapt prop passing if divergent (per the diff from step 1).</step>
    <step order="5" name="Delete local copy">Delete `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/src/components/CalendarSection.tsx`. If any other CalendarSidePane file imported the local copy, update them to import from the shared lib.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Build verification">Run `tsc --noEmit` + `npm run build` on `Spaarke.Events.Components` and `CalendarSidePane`. Verify 0 errors. Verify `@spaarke/events-components` exports resolve correctly.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Bundle-size measurement">Build CalendarSidePane and measure gzip bundle. Compare against pre-change baseline. Expected: similar size (the shared component may pull additional shared utilities — acceptable up to +50 KB; document if more).</step>
    <step order="8" name="Deploy">Deploy CalendarSidePane web resource via the appropriate deploy script (likely a script in `scripts/Deploy-*.ps1` or `code-page-deploy` skill — confirm at task start; CalendarSidePane is NOT a code page, it's a Power Pages / record-form embedded web resource).</step>
    <step order="9" name="Post-deploy visual smoke">Open CalendarSidePane on the same record forms used in step 2's snapshot. Compare against pre-change snapshot. Expected: IDENTICAL.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates">Invoke `code-review` skill and `adr-check` skill. Verify ADR-012 (no local divergent copy), ADR-021 (Fluent v9 tokens, no hex/rgba).</step>
    <step order="10" name="UI tests (parity + dark mode)">Invoke `ui-test` skill for the two tests defined below.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 055 status 🔲 → ✅.</step>
    <step order="12" name="Document deviations">If divergence between local and shared `CalendarSection` required a behavioral choice (e.g., different default prop value), document the resolution in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b6-divergence-resolution.md` for R4 lessons-learned.</step>
  </steps>

