  <ui-tests>
    <test name="CalendarSidePane parity with embedded Calendar (light + dark)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;etn=sprk_matter&amp;pagetype=entityrecord</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open a Matter record (with events linked to it) — CalendarSidePane should appear on the form</step>
        <step>Verify CalendarSection renders with events visible</step>
        <step>Compare side-by-side against SpaarkeAi embedded Calendar widget (same date range, same data) — expect visual parity</step>
        <step>Interact: click a date, expand an event chip, scroll to a different week</step>
        <step>Verify all interactions behave identically to the embedded Calendar widget</step>
        <step>Switch to dark mode in D365 settings</step>
        <step>Verify backgrounds, text colors, event chip colors adapt (no white-on-white, no black-on-black)</step>
        <step>Verify icons use currentColor (visible in dark mode)</step>
        <step>Verify no console errors or warnings</step>
        <step>Compare against pre-change snapshot — expect IDENTICAL</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>CalendarSidePane visually + behaviorally IDENTICAL to embedded Calendar widget. Dark mode compliant per ADR-021 (Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens only). No console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="No local divergent copy remains">
      <steps>
        <step>Run grep for `CalendarSection` in `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/`</step>
        <step>Verify there is NO file `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/src/components/CalendarSection.tsx`</step>
        <step>Verify all references to `CalendarSection` in CalendarSidePane import from `@spaarke/events-components`</step>
        <step>Run `tsc --noEmit` — 0 errors</step>
        <step>Run grep across the repo for ANY other local CalendarSection.tsx copies — verify none</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Single source of truth: `CalendarSection` exists ONLY in `@spaarke/events-components`. ADR-012 compliance verified.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given CalendarSidePane on a record form, When viewed alongside SpaarkeAi's embedded Calendar widget with the same data, Then they are visually + behaviorally IDENTICAL (FR-09 acceptance).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-012 (single source of truth), When the repo is grepped, Then `CalendarSection` exists ONLY in `@spaarke/events-components` — no local copy in `src/solutions/CalendarSidePane/`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-021 dark mode, When CalendarSidePane is viewed in dark mode, Then all colors adapt via Fluent v9 tokens — no white/black hardcoded.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the import in CalendarSidePane's App.tsx, When inspected, Then `CalendarSection` is imported from `@spaarke/events-components` (not from a local relative path).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given NFR-08 bundle-size budget, When CalendarSidePane gzip bundle is measured, Then delta vs pre-change baseline is ≤ +50 KB OR justified in notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `tsc --noEmit`, When run on CalendarSidePane and Spaarke.Events.Components, Then 0 type errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the deployed CalendarSidePane web resource, When opened on a record form post-deploy, Then it renders correctly + has 0 console errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

